body:
SPRING LOVE - MASHIHO

Genre // Fluff, romance.

AU // This is my first time posting one of my stories on here oof ╰(*´︶`*)╯♡ so if it’s bad; i’m sorry huuuuue. Feel free to request anything tho!

________ ________ ________ ________ ________

Spring, it’s warm and full of sun kissed flowers that brighten up anything in its eye of view. Nothing made you more happy than a day of sunny breeze, the wind slightly slapping gently on your face; bringing out the rosiness in your cold but heated cheeks.

A library is where you go to enjoy the day, even though it’s inside there’s a big mirror that gives you the perfect view to a empty yet beautiful park. What I told you, you only go to this library and this one specific seat for a certain reason.

Every other day, when you would visit the library, there was this boy. He was somewhat short but still had a big smile. His hair a soft chestnut colour and your typical soft boy clothing. You’ve never talked to him, you’ve just simply been fascinated by him. He’s always there, same spot, having the same picnic he did the previous day. Kinda similar to you.

Of course you’d never muster up the courage and talk to him, no. You were too introverted for this, you always chose to admire from afar. Besides, you wouldn’t get hurt if you never tried. You told yourself, actions aren’t always louder than words.

Whenever the weather was like this, you would make your trip to the library. You knew he’d be in the park having his picnic. Every time you walk up those stairs, your heart fuels a fire, as if you can taste the water going down a thirsty throat, right when it’s near. Except he wasn’t there.

Instead, you look over at your table, and see an unfamiliar presence, but you know that chestnut hair anywhere. The curly strands of hair that lapped over each other, so delicately like strands of grass in a open field of daisies.

You decide to make your way there, what’s the worse that colour happen?

The sweet silence fills the room, loud silence. I somewhat relaxed you. It gave you room to think, room to have a place of your own.

“You know, I never see you read anything.”

Something so soft spoke. Every particle of this persons made you blood stop and rush to your cheeks, you could nearly smell the rosiness. Your drift your eyes up, and he’s there. Right in front of you, his eyes are the brown of a tree trunk, but they have their own little sparkle. He was mesmerising, his cheekbones as edged as a knife, but his nose soft like a marshmallow. You couldn’t stop looking at him, he was ethereal in every essence of a person.

“Don’t think I don’t notice, I’m mashiho by the way. You are?”
